    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-15T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/2–1446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-15T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>253. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 436, Feb 9.<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d183fn1">Not printed.</note> Statement of US position re Podesta
                        Costa<note n="69" xml:id="d183fn2">Luis Podesta Costa, candidate for
                        judgeship, International Court of Justice.</note> is explained in separate
                    telegram. In your discretion you may use <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>
                    to clear up any misunderstanding.</p>
                <p>Secretary’s press comments today covered in separate telegram. (<gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 481, Feb 14)<note n="68" xml:id="d183fn3"
                        >Not printed.</note> Dept contemplates no statement for present since
                    obvious purpose Perón’s counter-charges is to divert attention from Blue Book by
                    inducing us to engage in debate on his allegations. We are accordingly
                    reiterating that the document speaks for itself.</p>
                <p>We are not at this time inclined to favor suggestion re publication of
                    documentation and do not wish to encourage requests by foreign Govts for such
                    action. Our statement has been submitted and we are awaiting receipt of other
                    Govts views (see final page of document).</p>
                <p>With reference to suggestion contained concluding sentence <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 490 Feb 14 while Dept does not wish to
                    limit your action in event sudden emergency development we hope you will at
                    least have opportunity to communicate with us by telephone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
